## Image Optimization Tips

### Compression Tools
- **TinyPNG** (https://tinypng.com) - Best for PNG compression
- **Squoosh** (https://squoosh.app) - Advanced compression with preview
- **ImageOptim** - Mac app for batch optimization
- **JPEG-Optimizer** - Online JPEG compression

### Format Guidelines
1. **Use JPG for:** Photos, product images with complex colors
2. **Use PNG for:** Images requiring transparency, simple graphics
3. **Consider WebP:** Modern format with 30% better compression (auto-handled by site)

### Naming Convention
Use descriptive, SEO-friendly names:
```
‚úÖ turmeric-powder-organic-100g.jpg
‚úÖ green-tea-leaves-premium.jpg
‚ùå IMG_1234.jpg
‚ùå photo.jpg
```

### Quality Settings
- **Product Cards:** 80-85% quality
- **Detail Images:** 85-90% quality
- **Thumbnails:** 75-80% quality
- **Hero Images:** 80-85% quality

## Usage Instructions

1. **Prepare Images:**
   - Resize to recommended dimensions
   - Compress using tools above
   - Use descriptive file names
   - Test on mobile devices

2. **Add to Project:**
   ```bash
   # Place files in this directory
   src/assets/products/your-image-name.jpg
   ```

3. **Import in Code:**
   ```typescript
   import productImage from '@/assets/products/turmeric-powder.jpg';
   ```

4. **Update Product Data:**
   ```typescript
   // In src/data/products.ts
   {
     id: "turmeric",
     name: "Organic Turmeric",
     image: productImage,
     images: [image1, image2, image3], // Multiple angles
     // ... other properties
   }
   ```

